<span id="freeTextContainer9466580518766632741">The book has a nice, extensive introduction with notes about the cultural background, the author and style, also a guide for further reading, ground plan maps, etc. but on the other hand e.g. omits to draw a parallel with the poem line: &quot;may these pebbles grow to mighty rocks&quot; and Kimigayo lyrics. In a word, I cannot discern how extensive and detailed the footnotes are.<br/><br/>Since the main text of the book is a classic just for the fact of its existence and circumstances of its origin, I will refrain </span>
  <span id="freeText9466580518766632741" style="display:none">The book has a nice, extensive introduction with notes about the cultural background, the author and style, also a guide for further reading, ground plan maps, etc. but on the other hand e.g. omits to draw a parallel with the poem line: "may these pebbles grow to mighty rocks" and Kimigayo lyrics. In a word, I cannot discern how extensive and detailed the footnotes are.<br /><br />Since the main text of the book is a classic just for the fact of its existence and circumstances of its origin, I will refrain from grading it. </span>
